nodes.documentation:
@dev Library used to query support of an interface declared via {IERC165}.
 * Note that these functions return the actual result of the query: they do not
`revert` if an interface is not supported. It is up to the caller to decide
what to do in these cases.
nodes.name: ERC165Checker

nodes.documentation: @dev Returns true if `account` supports the {IERC165} interface,
nodes.name: supportsERC165
supportsInterface

nodes.documentation:
@dev Returns true if `account` supports all the interfaces defined in
`interfaceIds`. Support for {IERC165} itself is queried automatically.
     * Batch-querying can lead to gas savings by skipping repeated checks for
{IERC165} support.
     * See {IERC165-supportsInterface}.
nodes.name: supportsAllInterfaces
_supportsERC165Interface
_callERC165SupportsInterface
